---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Stove Philosophy | Four Burners">
  <main class="mx-auto min-h-screen max-w-5xl px-6 py-14 sm:py-20">
    <section>
      <p
        class="inline-flex rounded-full border border-slate-700 bg-slate-900/70 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium tracking-wide text-slate-300"
      >
        The Four Burners of Life
      </p>
      <h1
        class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-6xl"
      >
        You have four burners and two hands. Do the math.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-base leading-7 text-slate-300 sm:text-lg">
        Family, work, health, and friends: the ancient Stoves teach that you
        cannot keep all four on high simultaneously. Accept this. Something must
        be set to simmer, or you&apos;ll scorch everything and order expensive
        takeout.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10 grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <article class="rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-5">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">High Heat (Choose Two)</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">
          Pick the burners that need immediate attention today. Not forever—just
          today. Philosophy is wise enough to know tomorrow&apos;s menu will
          change.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-5">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Simmer Without Shame</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">
          Simmering is not neglect; it&apos;s strategic heat management. A
          gentle bubble still cooks the stew and saves your eyebrows.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article
        class="rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-5 sm:col-span-2"
      >
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Daily Burner Checklist</h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">
          <li>
            • Family: Did I call, listen, or at least send a non-dry text?
          </li>
          <li>• Work: Did I do meaningful tasks, not just rearrange tabs?</li>
          <li>• Health: Did I move, hydrate, or consume something green?</li>
          <li>• Friends: Did I maintain a friendship beyond liking memes?</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
